From: typedrat <local-patch>
Subject: rustPlatform.importCargoLock: download crates from static.crates.io

crates.io has begun returning HTTP 403 from /api/v1/crates/.../download
for requests without a User-Agent header (a known long-standing crates.io
policy that is now strictly enforced). Nix's fetchurl does not send a UA,
which breaks every importCargoLock-based build (fenix's rust-analyzer,
local crates importing third-party Cargo.lock files, etc.).

Mirrors the fix in NixOS/nixpkgs#525067 (fetchCrate) for the legacy
importCargoLock path. static.crates.io is the CDN backing the same data
and does not require a User-Agent.

This patch is local to typedrat/nix-config until an equivalent upstream
PR lands.

---
 pkgs/build-support/rust/import-cargo-lock.nix | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/pkgs/build-support/rust/import-cargo-lock.nix b/pkgs/build-support/rust/import-cargo-lock.nix
--- a/pkgs/build-support/rust/import-cargo-lock.nix
+++ b/pkgs/build-support/rust/import-cargo-lock.nix
@@ -130,7 +130,7 @@
     };
 
   registries = {
-    "https://github.com/rust-lang/crates.io-index" = "https://crates.io/api/v1/crates";
+    "https://github.com/rust-lang/crates.io-index" = "https://static.crates.io/crates";
   }
   // extraRegistries;
 
